The existing formula is wrong because it uses an array-style IF comparison and returns only `C3` instead of summing matching values. A proper spreadsheet formula here is `SUMIFS` over the Net profit column with criteria on Year and Share No.

Next I will:
1. Load the workbook.
2. Write the corrected formula into K6, using absolute references to I3 and J3.
3. Save to the output path with the same filename.
4. Recalculate and verify that K6 evaluates to the expected value.
Code:
```repl
from openpyxl import load_workbook
import os, shutil

infile = input_spreadsheet
outfile = os.path.join("/sandbox/output/output_spreadsheet", os.path.basename(infile))
shutil.copy(infile, outfile)

wb = load_workbook(outfile)
ws = wb[wb.sheetnames[0]]

# Place corrected formula in K6
ws["K6"] = "=SUMIFS($C$3:$C$8,$A$3:$A$8,$I$3,$B$3:$B$8,$J$3)"

wb.save(outfile)
print("Saved to:", outfile)
print("Formula in K6:", ws["K6"].value)

# Recalculate and verify
recalc_result = await recalculate(outfile)
print("Recalc:", recalc_result)

wb_check = load_workbook(outfile, data_only=False)
ws_check = wb_check[wb_check.sheetnames[0]]
print("Stored formula K6:", ws_check["K6"].value)

wb_values = load_workbook(outfile, data_only=True)
ws_values = wb_values[wb_values.sheetnames[0]]
print("Cached value K6:", ws_values["K6"].value)

output_spreadsheet = outfile
```
